## Plan Summary

**Root cause:** Off-by-one error in `src/utils.ts`, line 7.

```typescript
// BUGGY — stops one iteration too early
for (let i = 0; i < items.length - 1; i++) {

// FIXED
for (let i = 0; i < items.length; i++) {
```

The `- 1` in the loop condition means the loop exits before reaching the last index, so the final element is never uppercased or pushed into `results`.

**Scope of change:** Single file, single line — remove `- 1` from the loop condition in `src/utils.ts`.

**Tests:** The existing test suite in `tests/utils.test.ts` already has 4 tests for `processItems` that cover this exact scenario (3-element array, single item, two items, and empty array). All 6 tests in the suite will pass once the fix is applied — no test changes needed.

